You are given the content of the variable <get_day_calendar_events_0/> which contains the list of calendar events for the day. Parse it and return only an integer number equal to the number of events that should be counted as scheduled appointments.

Counting rules: Count each element in the top-level list as one appointment unless it explicitly indicates it is canceled. Treat an event as canceled if any of the following are true:
- it has a key "status" whose value (case-insensitive) is "cancelled" or "canceled";
- it has a boolean key "is_cancelled" or "is_canceled" set to true;
- it has a key "canceled" set to true.

Return ONLY the integer number, with no extra text or formatting.

